board.com/umelchiathemad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Melchia The Mad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/3/01 5:53:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=475.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> PvP Question (New rogue)</span><hr size=1> I'm currently playing a dwarven rogue, lvl 17 (seems like I'm just starting to be able to PvP with other my range)<br>My question is, when fighting say, a warrior, and he's got see invis, you end up jousting. Now when I'm right on top of em half them time , it keeps saying &quot;Your target is too far away&quot;<br>Now, do you guys keep auto attack on all the time when fighting? (obviously not while hiding, sneaking) Or do you turn off and click on again when close to opponent?<br>I've seemed to had a little better luck with the latter.<br>Oh, when I hit 18-20, Is there anywhere where I can buy the poison ingrediants to make myself? (Vendor, not player)<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/3/01 9:06:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=475.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP Question (New rogue)</span><hr size=1> Oh well really all I can say about that bug is, welcome to EQ PvP. Whether you like to joust or just leave on attack is up to you, personally I always jousted though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=elegance>Elegance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/01 12:14:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=475.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP Question (New rogue)</span><hr size=1> lol unless your one filthy stinkin rich lvl 20 the answer is no on the poison supplies. you can go that route but its very very pricey. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uceescritdabossalini.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceescrit da Bossalini</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/01 11:35:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=475.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PvP Question (New rogue)</span><hr size=1> &quot;Now, do you guys keep auto attack on all the time when fighting? (obviously not while hiding, sneaking) Or do you turn off and click on again when close to opponent?&quot;<br><br>This is known as jousting.  The idea here, is to press auto attack (and backstab if its up), just as you pass through your opponent, and turn it off right after.  This way makes sure that you make every swing count in PvP.<br><br>The downside to this is, it gives somone with a high damage weapon (aka Warrior, SK, Ranger with a 2 HS) an large advantage.  The only way I've ever gotten around this, is to only make passes when backstab refreshes, and try to play keep away/bow kite the warrior in between.<br><br>As far as a poison goes, I started with root poison (components sold in WK).  It is kinda pricey though.  The only way I could afford to use it was to make my own vials, and farm stuff like batwings, bonechips, CB belts, etc. to raise funds for my poison and PvP habbit. <p><font size=4 face=Times New Roman, serif><b>Ceescrit Bossalini</font><BR>Retired Roag of VZ<BR><a href=http://www.eqrogue.com>Order of the Black Rose</b></a> <BR>--------------------------------<BR><i>"Let it be known, I'm troublesome!"</i></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showPrevMessage?topicID=475.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showNextMessage?topicID=475.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=475.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.emailToFriend?topicID=475.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.threadControl?topicID=475.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=475.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=475.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jum